<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 11:32PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of light snow overnight...
Periods of light snow will move through Central and Southwest MT
through 2 AM. Visibility could fall below one mile at times. New
snow accumulations will generally range from about one half inch
to around 1 inch.
Those traveling along I-90 from Butte to Bozeman Pass or around
the Boulder and White Sulphur Springs area should be prepared for
quickly changing road conditions and areas of poor visibility.</description>
